  },
  {
    "file": "charts/pawtograder/templates/web-channels.yaml",
    "line": 10,
    "summary": "No uniqueness guard on `.Values.channels[].name`. Two entries with the same name (or one differing only past the 63-char truncation point of componentName) render duplicate Service/Deployment/Ingress/Kong-route names.",
    "failure_scenario": "Operator copies a channel block and forgets to rename it, or uses two long names sharing a 53-char prefix that both truncate to the same `<fullname>-web-<...>` (trunc 63). The rendered manifest contains two objects with identical name+namespace+kind; `helm install` aborts with 'rendered manifests contain a resource that already exists' / duplicate-key, or one channel silently clobbers the other's Deployment. There is no `fail` that names the colliding channels."
  }
]
