    "path": "utils/supabase/middleware.ts",
    "line": 86,
    "body": "**The `classes` lookup swallows its error and fails *open* to stable.** Destructuring only `{ data: cls }` discards `error`; on any transient read failure (statement timeout, pool exhaustion, a brief RLS/role hiccup) `cls` is `null`, so `courseChannel` falls back to `'stable'`.\n\nOn a **canary** build (`currentChannel() === 'canary'`) that means a momentary DB glitch redirects the user off the canary host back to stable mid-session — and back to canary once the DB recovers — a visible flap, with no log or Sentry breadcrumb because the error was thrown away.\n\nCapture `error` and **fail closed** (stay on the current host when the lookup errors), and log it."
